13:54.710 --> 13:56.462
came from the mom, Amalia.

13:56.462 --> 13:58.843
Daniel was unaware it was happening.

13:58.843 --> 14:02.684
Amalia has no idea why Daniel
is leaving politics, nor do I.

14:02.684 --> 14:03.936
Sounds like you might.

14:05.063 --> 14:06.441
‐ [ knock on door ]

14:11.492 --> 14:13.831
‐ [ Pony whimpers ]
‐ Oh. Hey, hey. Hey.

14:13.831 --> 14:16.085
VERONICA: Sorry.
‐ That's okay. Dogs love me.

14:16.085 --> 14:18.507
They can intuit my strong moral center.

14:18.507 --> 14:20.678
And, plus, I usually smell like pepperoni.

14:20.678 --> 14:23.183
‐ [chuckles] I'd ask you to elaborate
on those feelings,

14:23.183 --> 14:25.521
but they'll be on <i>The View</i> later, right?

14:25.521 --> 14:30.113
‐ Oh, okay. Look, did you tell <i>me</i>
everything <i>you</i> knew about the case?

14:30.823 --> 14:33.244
Twelve‐inch cheese.

14:33.244 --> 14:34.957
I shoulda known this was a setup.

14:34.957 --> 14:36.961
‐ Why do you think it's Maloof?

14:36.961 --> 14:39.800
‐ Well, follow the money, Mars.

14:39.800 --> 14:41.971
And speaking of money,
this is $11.34.

14:43.766 --> 14:46.062
‐ Is the Tawny bribe all you have?

14:46.062 --> 14:49.402
Because if so, that is some thin crust,
my friend.

14:49.402 --> 14:52.074
‐ Okay, if you must know‐‐
LOGAN: Oh, she must.

14:53.076 --> 14:55.330
‐ If you must know, I'm waiting
on forensic results

14:55.330 --> 14:57.627
from a piece of shrapnel
that I think may prove

14:57.627 --> 15:00.508
to be the proverbial nail
in Maloof's coffin.

15:00.508 --> 15:03.639
‐ And I'm guessing this proverbial nail
is just a literal nail?

15:03.639 --> 15:08.481
‐ I'm unveiling the results
at the next Murderheads hive‐mind meeting.

15:08.481 --> 15:11.112
Come if you're curious.
Deets are on the web.

15:18.043 --> 15:19.420
‐ [ cell phone buzzing ]

15:20.338 --> 15:21.800
‐ This is for you.

15:23.470 --> 15:25.474
LOGAN: My mission,
should I choose to accept it,

15:25.474 --> 15:27.562
from the official king of spring break.

15:28.271 --> 15:31.779
‐ "9‐1‐1. Can you bring me pants?
P. S. This is Dick."

15:32.739 --> 15:34.033
Why does Dick needs pants?

15:34.033 --> 15:36.162
LOGAN: Why does he need
to tell me this is Dick?

15:36.162 --> 15:40.045
I assume any text that starts
with "bring me pants" is from Dick.

15:43.009 --> 15:45.430
Quacks is only nine blocks away.

15:45.430 --> 15:47.142
You feel like bein' a hero?

15:48.436 --> 15:51.067
‐ The owner did tell me
she would gather the security footage

15:51.067 --> 15:53.238
from the night before
the Sea Sprite bombing.

15:53.238 --> 15:56.745
‐ [ party sounds intensify ]
‐ [ mock sobs ]

15:56.745 --> 15:59.208
[ whimpers ]
‐ It'll stop soon.

16:01.462 --> 16:02.674
I'll get the pants.

16:04.218 --> 16:06.932
[ dance music playing ]

16:11.608 --> 16:14.113
‐ That's fake Dick.
‐ That's the worst kind.

16:14.113 --> 16:15.908
‐ [ microphone feeds back ]

16:15.908 --> 16:19.248
[ speaks Russian ]
‐ <i>That's</i> real Dick.

16:19.248 --> 16:21.002
DICK: Czar Casablancas...
‐ I take that back.

16:21.002 --> 16:23.632
DICK: ...quackin' atcha tonight!
Yeah! Quack!

16:23.632 --> 16:25.427
CROWD: Yeah!
‐ Quack‐quack‐quack‐quack!

16:25.427 --> 16:29.936
Now, due to some new city ordinances,
tonight's dance competition will proceed

16:29.936 --> 16:32.734
without any sexualized content
whatsoever.

16:32.734 --> 16:35.907
‐ [ crowd booing ]
‐ Just hear us out, okay?

16:35.907 --> 16:38.453
What we're lookin' for is something...
tasteful.

16:38.453 --> 16:39.873
Something classy.

16:39.873 --> 16:42.962
Something, I don't know, like this.

16:42.962 --> 16:46.427
[ dance music plays ]

16:46.427 --> 16:48.891
‐ [ crowd cheering ]

16:51.479 --> 16:54.986
SINGER:
<i>♪ Jet set sex sessions ♪</i>

16:54.986 --> 16:56.740
<i>♪ Dance party, sexy bodies ♪</i>

16:56.740 --> 17:00.413
[ crowd cheering ]

17:00.413 --> 17:02.334
<i>♪ Don't they know the shit</i>
<i>they started? ♪</i>

17:02.334 --> 17:04.171
‐ Whoooo!

17:04.171 --> 17:07.469
‐ I still don't get why he needs‐‐
‐ [ crowd cheering ]

17:07.469 --> 17:08.889
‐ Spoke too soon.

17:11.018 --> 17:15.443
‐ [ crowd cheering ]

17:15.443 --> 17:17.489
[ music continues, muffled ]

17:20.871 --> 17:22.542
‐ Ah, look who's here.

17:22.542 --> 17:24.336
Bet you want the security footage,
don't you?

17:24.336 --> 17:25.965
‐ I do.
NICOLE: Mm‐hmm.

17:28.303 --> 17:31.017
You don't have a drink.
That will not do.

17:34.064 --> 17:35.943
[ bottles clinking ]

17:35.943 --> 17:37.780
‐ Going to the opera later?

17:38.782 --> 17:41.997
‐ Yeah, those make a guest appearance
in the video.

17:43.542 --> 17:46.548
‐ Wow. Weighted and ridged
for his displeasure.

17:46.548 --> 17:51.057
‐ [ laughs ]
All right. Here you go.

17:51.683 --> 17:53.102
‐ Thank you.
‐ Cheers.

17:54.564 --> 17:56.192
‐ [ door opens ]
DICK: Hey, hey!

17:57.027 --> 17:58.530
Ahoy, ladies!

17:58.530 --> 18:00.785
‐ Wait, aren't you supposed to be
judging a dance contest right now?

18:00.785 --> 18:02.955
‐ Oh, no, you gotta give it
at least 45 minutes.

18:02.955 --> 18:05.670
That way the kids
can buy a shit‐ton of drinks.

18:05.670 --> 18:07.840
‐ Oh. Sometimes I really like you.

18:07.840 --> 18:10.470
‐ I would marry you right now.
I can get a ring.

18:10.470 --> 18:12.391
Hey, Logan. Ring. Got one?

18:13.059 --> 18:14.896
Ow! [ laughs ]
‐ Well, pace yourself.

18:14.896 --> 18:17.025
Let's see how well you represent
the Quacks at the volleyball tournament

18:17.025 --> 18:18.570
this weekend.
‐ That is fair.

18:18.570 --> 18:20.991
Ah, that reminds me. You are playing
volleyball with me this weekend,

18:20.991 --> 18:22.787
so, uh, try to get in shape, huh?

18:22.787 --> 18:25.166
Pyoo pyoo! Ohh‐ho‐ho! God!

18:25.166 --> 18:26.252
NICOLE:
Okay.

18:27.839 --> 18:29.049
Who's up for some E?

18:32.139 --> 18:34.728
‐ Me? Yeah. I mean, I've been rollin'
for 72 hours. Yes.

18:34.728 --> 18:37.482
[ dance music playing ]

18:37.482 --> 18:39.153
‐ [ crowd cheering ]

18:45.750 --> 18:47.377
‐ [ whooshing ]

18:47.377 --> 18:48.839
‐ Ha ha ha! Yo!

18:51.093 --> 18:52.722
Ohhhh!

18:52.722 --> 18:55.101
‐ Hey, play <i>No Scrubs!</i>

18:55.101 --> 18:56.187
[ record scratches ]

18:56.187 --> 18:57.899
[ all singing along ]
♪ I don't want no scrub ♪

18:57.899 --> 19:01.155
♪ A scrub is a guy
that can't get no love from me ♪

19:01.155 --> 19:04.453
♪ Hangin' out the passenger side
of his best friend's ride ♪

19:04.453 --> 19:06.541
♪ Tryin' to holla at me ♪

19:10.800 --> 19:12.595
‐ Care to join me in my study?

19:12.595 --> 19:16.645
VERONICA: [ retching, coughing ]
‐ That tracks.

19:16.645 --> 19:18.565
‐ [ toilet flushing ]

19:19.441 --> 19:20.443
‐ Ohh.

19:21.988 --> 19:24.159
Ooh.
‐ [ knocking on door ]

19:26.790 --> 19:28.251
[ knocking ]

19:31.633 --> 19:34.137
VERONICA: [ sighs ] Hmm.
‐ [ knocking ]

19:36.601 --> 19:38.479
‐ [ gags ] Ohh.

19:38.479 --> 19:40.149
[ clears throat ]

19:43.364 --> 19:46.203
‐ Puffy face,
liquor seeping from the pores,

19:46.203 --> 19:49.376
hints of B. O. , and am I‐‐
am I detecting...

19:51.088 --> 19:53.342
...rancid vomit?

19:53.342 --> 19:55.931
Ohh.
‐ Why are you here?

19:55.931 --> 19:58.604
‐ I found our rat guy.

19:58.604 --> 20:00.816
Uniform is from Dobie's Sweet Release,

20:00.816 --> 20:04.156
that bakery on the edge of town
that hires only ex‐cons.

20:05.199 --> 20:07.370
I was <i>gonna</i> see
if you wanted to come with,

20:07.370 --> 20:09.333
maybe buy you a <i>croissant.</i>

20:09.333 --> 20:10.335
‐ Ohh.

20:11.211 --> 20:15.846
Was thinking I'd Postmate
a shit‐ton of <i>pain du francais</i>

20:15.846 --> 20:19.061
and watch the Comrade Quacks
security footage.

20:19.061 --> 20:21.190
I picked it up last night.
[ grunts ]

20:21.190 --> 20:23.319
SPRING BREAKER:
What's up, V‐card?

20:23.319 --> 20:24.781
VERONICA:
Hey, Jackson!

20:25.741 --> 20:27.160
[ chuckles ]

20:27.160 --> 20:28.496
That's Jackson.

20:28.496 --> 20:30.584
We danced last night.
He's cool.

20:30.584 --> 20:32.546
‐ Yeah. Jackson's the best.

20:40.896 --> 20:42.273
‐ Anything good on there?

20:42.273 --> 20:44.111
‐ Helpful? No.

20:44.111 --> 20:46.031
Entertaining? Yeah.

20:48.160 --> 20:49.539
Check this out.

20:52.252 --> 20:54.006
ONLOOKERS:
<i>Whoa!</i>

20:54.006 --> 20:55.676
‐ Ooh.
VERONICA: Right?

20:55.676 --> 20:57.137
Pow! Right in the kisser.

20:57.137 --> 20:59.141
‐ Wow! What a right hook!

20:59.141 --> 21:00.435
What does‐‐ What does she have
on her hand?

21:00.435 --> 21:01.855
‐ A sap glove.

21:01.855 --> 21:04.443
And remember that.
Sap. Glove.

21:04.443 --> 21:05.779
Because that's what I want
for Christmas.

21:05.779 --> 21:07.533
The knuckles are filled with BBs.

21:07.533 --> 21:08.618
‐ It's too late.

21:08.618 --> 21:10.956
I picked out a really cute
puke bucket for ya,

21:10.956 --> 21:12.333
spared no expense.

21:12.333 --> 21:14.254
It's got our family crest on it,

21:14.254 --> 21:16.634
a calligrapher is adding
the family motto.

21:16.634 --> 21:20.601
‐ Ohh. "We used to be disgusted,
now we try to be amused"?

21:20.601 --> 21:24.357
Ohh! I'm gonna be the envy
of everyone at the vomitorium.

21:24.357 --> 21:27.823
‐ So nothing useful on the Comrade Quacks
surveillance video, huh?

21:27.823 --> 21:32.875
‐ No. But I did find Jimmy Hatfield
on a registered sex offender list.

21:32.875 --> 21:35.004
So I'll look into that.

21:35.004 --> 21:36.841
Um, did you slay the rat king?

21:36.841 --> 21:39.847
‐ I did. I located him,
he confessed.

21:39.847 --> 21:41.475
Said he was releasing the rats

21:41.475 --> 21:44.272
because Hu'$ Reduced
sold him a bad steak.

21:44.272 --> 21:46.318
‐ That seems like a bit
of an overreaction, don't you think?

21:46.318 --> 21:48.489
‐ I do.
‐ [ knock on door ]

21:48.489 --> 21:49.659
‐ Hello?

21:51.161 --> 21:52.080
MATTY: Hi.

21:52.080 --> 21:55.128
Oh‐‐
‐ Uh, Dad, this is Matty.

21:55.128 --> 21:57.298
‐ I recognize her from the Sea Sprite.

21:58.092 --> 22:01.558
I'm Keith Mars.
I'm sorry for your loss. Truly.

22:03.144 --> 22:04.730
‐ Thanks.

22:05.356 --> 22:07.528
So I, uh...

22:07.528 --> 22:09.114
I read up on you guys.

22:09.114 --> 22:12.830
My physics teacher vouches for you,
and Penn thinks you're legit.

22:12.830 --> 22:14.750
‐ The pizza guy?
‐ Phew.

22:14.750 --> 22:16.588
We'll sleep easy tonight.
MATTY: Well, he,

22:16.588 --> 22:19.301
uh, he dabbles in solving cold cases.

22:19.301 --> 22:22.140
‐ Yeah, he told us. Once or twice.

22:22.140 --> 22:24.562
‐ He's flaky, though.

22:24.562 --> 22:29.196
He's convinced JonBenét Ramsey
was killed by an owl, so...

22:29.196 --> 22:30.532
here I am.

22:32.202 --> 22:35.959
You told me Alpha‐Jolly
was a criminal hangout, right?

22:35.959 --> 22:36.961
‐ It sure is.

22:38.255 --> 22:42.096
‐ I think a guy there may have planted
the bomb at the Sea Sprite.

22:42.096 --> 22:43.934
‐ Matty, please. Sit.

22:47.524 --> 22:50.238
‐ Alpha‐Jolly handles
our vending machines,

22:50.238 --> 22:54.204
but the week of the bombing,
some guy we didn't know came.

22:54.204 --> 22:56.500
There was just something
really off about him.

22:56.500 --> 22:58.672
‐ Matty, do you mind my asking you,

22:58.672 --> 23:01.301
did your dad have any enemies
that you knew about?

23:03.097 --> 23:06.521
‐ Well, I'm guessing whoever was shitting
in our ice machines every few days

23:06.521 --> 23:09.527
wasn't a fan.
‐ Probably a solid assumption.

23:13.200 --> 23:16.958
‐ The guy from Alpha‐Jolly‐‐
think you'd still recognize him?

23:16.958 --> 23:19.797
‐ Most definitely.
He had this mole.

23:21.049 --> 23:22.553
‐ Do you get bored easily?

23:22.553 --> 23:23.888
‐ No.

23:23.888 --> 23:25.642
‐ Perfect.

23:30.736 --> 23:32.488
[ sighs ]

23:46.391 --> 23:49.105
‐ When your friend was... murdered...

23:50.776 --> 23:51.944
were you angry?

23:56.036 --> 23:57.664
‐ I'm still angry.

24:00.211 --> 24:01.589
‐ Good.

24:05.514 --> 24:07.433
My dad was all I had.

24:22.506 --> 24:23.758
‐ Here.

24:24.802 --> 24:26.806
You'll recognize Mole Man.

24:26.806 --> 24:29.436
You, uh, just focus here, and, um,

24:29.436 --> 24:31.064
just press this button.

24:35.281 --> 24:38.162
‐ So how‐‐ how do I take a selfie?

24:39.832 --> 24:41.251
[ laughs ]

24:41.251 --> 24:42.713
It's too easy.

24:50.812 --> 24:51.981
My God! That‐‐

24:51.981 --> 24:53.025
That's him!

24:54.027 --> 24:55.446
[ clicking ]

24:59.162 --> 25:00.289
[ soft chuckle ]

25:00.289 --> 25:02.043
‐ You got him?
‐ Yep.

25:03.378 --> 25:04.464
‐ Nice.

25:05.509 --> 25:08.598
Okay, here's how we get extra credit.

25:13.775 --> 25:15.444
‐ [ car door opens ]

25:17.533 --> 25:18.868
‐ [ camera clicking ]

25:19.870 --> 25:24.170
[ grunts ]
I'm gonna send these to my dad.

25:24.170 --> 25:25.632
Make him do the legwork.

25:27.385 --> 25:31.059
‐ So, you got some fun plans tonight?

25:31.059 --> 25:35.025
‐ Whatever the opposite of fun plans is...

25:35.025 --> 25:36.319
that's what I have.

25:40.494 --> 25:42.791
SALLY: <i>Yeah?</i>
‐ Hi, Ms. Mais?

25:42.791 --> 25:46.172
There's been an accident
involving your Nissan, license plate

25:46.172 --> 25:49.387
4‐V‐A, G‐zero‐zero,

25:49.387 --> 25:52.351
with a male driver who has no ID.

25:52.351 --> 25:55.650
We were hoping
you could help identify him.

25:55.650 --> 25:58.405
SALLY: <i>That's funny,</i>
<i>because my car is parked right outside.</i>

25:58.405 --> 26:00.827
<i>I tell you what, try to pull</i>
<i>some scam on me again,</i>

26:00.827 --> 26:02.998
<i>and I'll hunt you down</i>
<i>and shoot you dead.</i>

26:02.998 --> 26:05.670
<i>I work at the gun club, mister,</i>
<i>and I don't miss. [ disconnects ]</i>

26:05.670 --> 26:07.465
WOMAN:
<i>Neptune Gun Club.</i>

26:07.465 --> 26:09.637
‐ Hi, can I please speak with Sally Mais?

26:09.637 --> 26:11.431
WOMAN: <i>No, sorry,</i>
<i>she's not here right now.</i>

26:11.431 --> 26:14.897
‐ No? Well, maybe you can help me.

26:14.897 --> 26:18.111
I work at AMFTPG Financial Services,

26:18.111 --> 26:22.411
and I'm trying to verify some charges made
at Mo Chub's Gentlemen's Club.

26:22.411 --> 26:25.000
WOMAN: <i>Ugh.</i>
KEITH: Now, these don't fit

26:25.000 --> 26:27.213
Ms. Mais' previous spending patterns.

26:27.213 --> 26:28.925
WOMAN:
<i>No, I would guess not.</i>

26:28.925 --> 26:32.264
‐ Yeah, um, between you and me,
it usually turns out to be

26:32.264 --> 26:37.024
a freeloading boyfriend
or a son that gets a wild hare...

26:38.986 --> 26:41.116
WOMAN:
<i>That does sound like Perry.</i>

26:41.116 --> 26:44.247
‐ Right, Perry.
I see a charge right here.

26:44.247 --> 26:47.169
Uh, some dental work for Perry Anderson.

26:47.169 --> 26:49.967
WOMAN: <i>No, I'm talking about Perry Walsh.</i>
<i>Her boyfriend?</i>

26:49.967 --> 26:51.637
‐ Yeah, of course.

26:51.637 --> 26:54.560
Perry Anderson is the name
of the dentist.

26:54.560 --> 26:56.605
Great. Thanks so much.

26:56.605 --> 26:58.316
Bye.
WOMAN: <i>Bye.</i>

27:11.301 --> 27:12.721
‐ [ tapping keys ]

27:13.765 --> 27:15.685
Sweet Jesus.

27:19.735 --> 27:21.572
‐ Keith. What do you want? I‐‐

27:21.572 --> 27:23.241
‐ The guy who was temporarily tending

27:23.241 --> 27:25.997
to the vending machines
at the Sea Sprite last week?

27:25.997 --> 27:27.249
Perry Walsh.

27:28.335 --> 27:29.880
‐ What about him?

27:29.880 --> 27:31.967
‐ He did a stint in Chino two years ago

27:31.967 --> 27:34.138
for sending a package bomb
to his ex‐girlfriend.

27:34.138 --> 27:37.019
‐ I personally interviewed everyone
on Alpha‐Jolly's payroll.

27:37.019 --> 27:38.606
There was no Perry Walsh on it.

27:40.442 --> 27:44.033
‐ Here's a picture of him walking out
of Alpha‐Jolly five hours ago.

27:47.541 --> 27:49.628
‐ Okay. Thanks, Keith.

27:51.297 --> 27:52.759
We'll look into it.

28:00.567 --> 28:02.278
Is he gone?

28:06.160 --> 28:08.833
‐ He's gone.
‐ Get a SWAT team mobilized <i>now.</i>

28:14.761 --> 28:18.561
‐ You should have everything you need,
but if you don't, call me.

28:19.521 --> 28:21.107
Do not answer the door.

28:21.107 --> 28:23.194
‐ [ sports game playing on TV ]
‐ Have fun, Logan.

28:24.280 --> 28:25.575
I'll be fine.

28:28.539 --> 28:30.752
‐ [ door opens, closes ]

28:30.752 --> 28:31.962
‐ Hmm.

28:46.240 --> 28:50.332
‐ Veronica Mars and Logan Echolls.
Wow.

28:50.332 --> 28:52.169
People are gonna lose their minds.

28:52.169 --> 28:54.423
‐ Do I know you?
‐ Uh, you should.

28:54.423 --> 28:57.346
I'm in the zeitgeist. So‐‐

28:57.346 --> 28:59.768
Uh, could you take your shoes off first?

28:59.768 --> 29:01.437
Thank you.

29:01.437 --> 29:02.982
‐ [ shoes clatter ]

29:05.697 --> 29:06.532
[ door closes ]

29:06.532 --> 29:09.621
PENN:
All right. Fellow Murderheads.

29:09.621 --> 29:13.378
As promised,
I would like to introduce, um...

29:13.378 --> 29:15.717
DON [ via videochat ]:
<i>Veronica Mars.</i>

29:15.717 --> 29:18.012
<i>And a fun bonus, Logan Echolls,</i>

29:18.012 --> 29:21.310
<i>one‐time boyfriend</i>
<i>of the Notorious D. L. K.</i>

29:21.310 --> 29:22.479
‐ D. L. K.?

29:22.479 --> 29:23.983
‐ <i>Dead Lilly Kane.</i>

29:23.983 --> 29:25.611
CAROL:
Oh, God. Don!

29:25.611 --> 29:27.782
‐ Don't forget.
Son of the murderer.

29:27.782 --> 29:29.118
‐ Well, so say some.

29:29.118 --> 29:32.792
‐ <i>Welcome. I'm Don.</i>
<i>I wish I could be there in person,</i>

29:32.792 --> 29:36.382
<i>but Congress is in session‐‐</i>
‐ Let me handle the introductions, Don.

29:36.382 --> 29:38.386
‐ Are you guys... together? Or...

29:38.386 --> 29:40.641
DON [ laughing ]:
<i>Of course they are, Carol.</i>

29:40.641 --> 29:41.935
<i>After what they've been through,</i>

29:41.935 --> 29:44.398
<i>they're both too damaged</i>
<i>to be with anyone else.</i>

29:44.398 --> 29:46.653
PENN: So, introductions.

29:46.653 --> 29:50.661
Uh, the man right here
elbow deep in the cornichons is Herc,

29:50.661 --> 29:54.210
he is a forensics expert
and also a night watchman

29:54.210 --> 29:55.378
at the Rosly Mall.

29:55.378 --> 29:57.801
Why don't you guys grab some seats,
okay?

29:59.178 --> 30:02.936
‐ We are here to talk about the bombing
at the Sea Sprite.

30:02.936 --> 30:06.527
Also, I was promised forensic evidence.

30:06.527 --> 30:09.365
‐ Okay, well, uh, first off,
I think it is pretty damning

30:09.365 --> 30:11.578
that the Maloofs have not released
a statement.

30:11.578 --> 30:13.289
