44:05.661 --> 44:08.751
I don't want it to look like
we're bilking the Maloofs off a hunch.

44:10.880 --> 44:12.466
‐ You don't feel it?

44:12.466 --> 44:14.261
‐ Barely. It's a whisper.

44:17.894 --> 44:20.566
‐ All right. Let's take the win.

44:26.912 --> 44:28.248
‐ Are you all right?

44:28.958 --> 44:31.462
‐ I'm so dumb.
I hit my head on the mirror,

44:31.462 --> 44:33.634
then drove my toe
into the sink last night.

44:33.634 --> 44:35.847
I know. "Turn on the lights."

44:37.934 --> 44:40.940
‐ But on a positive note,
he hasn't begged for a cigarette all day.

44:40.940 --> 44:43.571
‐ [ laughs ]
KEITH: Thank you.

44:43.571 --> 44:47.411
‐ So‐‐ So you really think
they got the right guy?

44:47.411 --> 44:48.873
‐ Yes.

44:54.551 --> 44:56.262
‐ No.

45:05.113 --> 45:09.121
SINGER:
<i>♪ Fairy tales can come true ♪</i>

45:09.121 --> 45:12.419
<i>♪ It can happen to you ♪</i>

45:12.419 --> 45:14.131
<i>♪ If you're young at heart ♪</i>

45:15.843 --> 45:17.597
DOCTOR:
Keith Mars?

45:17.597 --> 45:21.980
Hi. Dr. Mitchell.
Why don't you come on back?

45:21.980 --> 45:24.653
‐ Oh, I haven't filled out any forms.
‐ It's been handled.

45:24.653 --> 45:26.615
We have all your charts
from your previous doctors.

45:26.615 --> 45:28.117
We'll go over 'em together.

45:28.117 --> 45:30.163
SINGER:
<i>♪ You can go to extremes... ♪</i>

45:30.163 --> 45:34.338
‐ I'd like you to keep a record
of when your memory fails...

45:34.338 --> 45:37.260
so that we can track it
and get more information.

45:37.260 --> 45:40.643
And call me the next time
you have an episode.

45:40.643 --> 45:43.565
My email and cell are on the back.

45:43.565 --> 45:45.068
Just any time, day or night.

45:45.068 --> 45:46.655
‐ Would you like earbuds?

45:48.575 --> 45:51.288
SINGER:
<i>♪ Or on a swing ♪</i>

45:51.288 --> 45:52.709
<i>♪ Don't you know that it‐‐ ♪</i>

45:52.709 --> 45:55.255
<i>[ rock music playing ]</i>

45:57.969 --> 46:00.265
SINGER:
<i>♪ My girl, yeah, hey! ♪</i>

46:09.199 --> 46:10.828
WEEVIL:
Yo, who's cookin'?

46:10.828 --> 46:13.166
HECTOR:
One of the new kids.

46:13.166 --> 46:16.506
‐ No. Paul needs to be on the grill...

46:16.506 --> 46:17.842
'cause this tastes like

46:17.842 --> 46:21.098
some peculiar‐ass shit.
‐ [ laughter ]

46:21.098 --> 46:23.227
‐ Weevil!
WEEVIL: Huh?

46:23.227 --> 46:24.898
‐ Your sister wants you
to meet someone.

46:24.898 --> 46:28.864
‐ Bring him over.
‐ [ party chatter ]

46:36.003 --> 46:39.343
‐ So you're Alonzo.
Glad you could make it.

46:39.343 --> 46:40.971
Heard a lot about you.

46:40.971 --> 46:44.061
‐ Not a lot. Just‐‐ Just a normal amount.

46:48.194 --> 46:51.660
‐ Hey, uh, C, why don't you
put Paul on the grill for me, huh?

46:51.660 --> 46:53.496
He likes you. Please?

46:53.496 --> 46:54.582
Thank you.

46:56.127 --> 46:59.216
You up from Mexico on business?
‐ Yeah.

46:59.216 --> 47:03.559
‐ Look, your visit doesn't have
anything to do with the bombings, does it?

47:03.559 --> 47:06.105
‐ We didn't set off any bombs, man.

47:06.105 --> 47:07.692
I promise you that.

47:07.692 --> 47:10.321
‐ That wasn't the question. But okay.

47:10.321 --> 47:14.079
Don't break her heart,
and we'll be fine.

47:19.757 --> 47:21.051
CLAUDIA:
Hey.

47:21.051 --> 47:23.014
‐ Oh.
CLAUDIA: Everything good?

47:23.014 --> 47:24.767
‐ Yeah. Nice guy.

47:26.312 --> 47:30.571
‐ Hidey‐ho, Neptune. 'Tis I,
your king of spring break,

47:30.571 --> 47:33.451
Dick Casablancas!

47:33.451 --> 47:36.498
‐ [ all cheering ]
DICK: Ha ha ha!

47:36.498 --> 47:39.213
Now, who here has already seen
<i>Catalina Heat?</i>

47:39.213 --> 47:41.008
‐ [ all cheering ]
DICK: All right.

47:41.008 --> 47:44.056
Well, looks like my buddy here
brought his six‐pack with him.

47:44.056 --> 47:47.020
‐ [ crowd cheering ]
‐ Whoo!

47:47.020 --> 47:48.105
‐ So I brought mine.

47:49.024 --> 47:53.659
All right. Who's ready to watch us
block out with our cocks out?

47:53.659 --> 47:56.372
‐ Whoo!
DICK: Free ball while we free ball?

47:56.372 --> 47:59.587
Stuff these chicks while we‐‐
well, you get the idea, huh?

47:59.587 --> 48:01.633
But where is the other team?

48:01.633 --> 48:05.306
La‐la‐la‐la‐ladies!
Where you at? Ha ha!

48:05.306 --> 48:06.935
‐ [ crowd cheering ]

48:09.983 --> 48:12.153
DICK:
Oh my G‐‐ Ohhh.

48:12.153 --> 48:13.907
Well, this won't be
the first time I've said this,

48:13.907 --> 48:16.370
but, uh, I'm here for your daughters.

48:16.370 --> 48:17.455
Let's get it on!

48:17.455 --> 48:18.959
‐ [ whistle blows ]
‐ Is that who they're playing?

48:18.959 --> 48:22.048
How old are they?
Is this an even match?

48:22.842 --> 48:24.554
‐ No, it is not.

48:25.806 --> 48:28.394
Come on, boys! Be the ball!

48:28.394 --> 48:30.398
‐ [ referee blows whistle ]
SINGER: <i>♪ It's where I wanna be ♪</i>

48:30.398 --> 48:34.239
<i>♪ It's where I wanna be ♪</i>

48:34.239 --> 48:35.826
<i>♪ It's where I wanna be ♪</i>
DICK: Ohh!

48:35.826 --> 48:39.834
SINGER:
<i>♪ It's where I wanna be ♪</i>

48:39.834 --> 48:41.504
<i>♪ You know I'm ready ♪</i>

48:41.504 --> 48:44.927
‐ [ explosion ]
‐ [ people screaming ]

48:44.927 --> 48:46.890
VERONICA:
<i>I could have assured Alex Maloof</i>

48:46.890 --> 48:49.937
<i>that the person responsible</i>
<i>for his fiancée's death</i>

48:49.937 --> 48:52.359
<i>was killed in a bomb of his own making,</i>

48:52.359 --> 48:55.365
<i>that her death was senseless and random.</i>

48:55.365 --> 48:57.373
[ somber singing ]

48:59.373 --> 49:01.961
<i>And we could have taken a win for a win.</i>

49:03.172 --> 49:06.345
<i>But then that next bomb went off...</i>

49:06.345 --> 49:11.313
<i>and all I could think was:</i>
<i>"Holy shit. I was right."</i>

49:15.781 --> 49:18.035
<i>Why do I always have to be right?</i>

49:19.794 --> 49:20.834
[ low music ]
